		<div class="about_us_faq">
			Other delivery services offer multiple menu choices. Why don't you?
		</div>
		<div class="about_us_faq_body">
			<p>Think of the restaurant you eat at most often.</p>
			<p>Now think about the last several items you ordered at that restaurant.</p>
			<p>Chances are that you can count on one hand the number of unique things you ate. If that sounds familiar, it's because
			when most people familiarize themselves with a menu at a favorite restaurant, they know what they like, and the
			rest is just a distraction.</p>
			<p>Our goal is for you to trust us to craft a delicious meal for you every day you want it. We feel confident that we
			can do that, because we put all our attention into a few items, as opposed to a little attention into several items,
			most of which you don't want anyway.</p>
			<p>Menus are rotated on a daily basis, so you're never eating the same thing two days in a row.</p>
			<p>Each day's menu is posted in advance, so you can easily view what we will be serving on a particular day. If you don't
			like it, simply opt out that day, and we will try to do better the next time. We don't expect this to happen often,
			but if it does, we would appreciate you letting us know, so we can make it better.</p>
